26:04.420 --> 26:11.380
So we assume that you folks care about privacy and about security, and that means that you

26:11.380 --> 26:13.260
should be thinking about protecting data.

26:13.260 --> 26:18.060
And there's all sorts of lots of different types of data you might want to be protecting

26:18.060 --> 26:22.660
or your employers might want to be protecting or your governments, whoever it might be.

26:22.660 --> 26:27.100
And one thing I want to dispel is it's not about DRM.

26:27.100 --> 26:29.900
So confidential computing, when it first came along, people were very worried about it in

26:29.900 --> 26:34.100
